article.headline: Gaddy has 24 as Tarleton State beats Loyola Marymount 79-66

images.name: Jakorie Smith drills long 3-pointer vs. Loyola Marymount Lions
images.caption: Jakorie Smith drills long 3-pointer vs. Loyola Marymount Lions

article.linkText: Gaddy has 24 as Tarleton State beats Loyola Marymount 79-66
article.story: LOS ANGELES -- — Kiandre Gaddy had 24 points in Tarleton State's 79-66 victory over Loyola Marymount on Friday night. Gaddy added 12 rebounds for the Texans (9-4). Jakorie Smith scored 21 points and added five assists. Devon Barnes was 3-of-7 shooting, including 1 for 3 from 3-point range, and went 6 for 6 from the foul line to finish with 13 points. Justin Wright led the Lions (7-7) in scoring, finishing with 18 points. Keli Leaupepe added 16 points and two steals for Loyola Marymount. In addition, Dominick Harris had 15 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
